 "cells": [

   "metadata": {

   },
   "source": [
    "# Uso y manipulación de curvas"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "En este archivo se muestra como:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Obtener curvas desde la base de datos.\n",
    "- Graficar la curva con factores de descuento y tasa.\n",
    "- Calcular una curva sintética.\n",
    "- Crear una curva con configuración personalizada."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Configuración Inicial\n",
    "\n",
    "Comenzamos cargando las librerías necesarias"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2023-10-11T20:36:28.437513300Z",
     "start_time": "2023-10-11T20:36:26.874946900Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from finrisklib.data.dbreader import DBReader\n",
    "from finrisklib.market.curve import generate_curve_config\n",
    "from finrisklib.market.curve import Curve\n",
    "from finrisklib.enums import InterpolationMethod\n",
    "from finrisklib.enums import ExtrapolationMethod\n",
    "from finrisklib.enums import Compounding\n",
    "from finrisklib.enums import DayCount\n",
    "from finrisklib.enums import Source\n",
    "from datetime import date\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Carga desde base de datos\n",
    "\n",
    "Para cargar una curva desde base de datos son necesarios dos datos, la fecha y el código de la curva. Adicionalmente, se puede elegir entre cargar las curvas de Murex (Default) o las curvas oficiales."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2023-10-11T20:36:29.360086100Z",
     "start_time": "2023-10-11T20:36:28.437513300Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Definimos la fecha a la que se cargarán los datos\n",
    "curve_date = date(year=2022, month=8, day=23)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Códigos de las curvas a cargar\n",
    "murex_code = 'USD SOFR'\n",
    "bac_code = 'CURVA_USD_USA'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Inicializamos el lector de base de datos\n",
    "reader = DBReader()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Obtención de curvas\n",
    "murex_curve = reader.get_single_curve_data(curve_name=murex_code, process_date=curve_date, source=Source.SANDBOX)\n",
    "bac_curve = reader.get_single_curve_data(curve_name=bac_code, process_date=curve_date, source=Source.OFFICIAL)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Graficar curva\n",
    "\n",
    "Habiendo obtenido las curvas desde base de datos procedemos a graficarlas:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2023-10-11T20:36:29.581089600Z",
     "start_time": "2023-10-11T20:36:29.360086100Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>",
      "image/png": ""
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Gráfico de factores de descuento\n",
    "\n",
    "curve_dict = murex_curve.to_dict()\n",
    "\n",
    "tenors = curve_dict.keys()\n",
    "dfs = curve_dict.values()\n",
    "plt.scatter(tenors, dfs)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2023-10-11T20:36:29.733301900Z",
     "start_time": "2023-10-11T20:36:29.565463700Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>",
      "image/png": ""
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Gráfico de tasas\n",
    "\n",
    "rates_dict = murex_curve.rates_to_dict()\n",
    "\n",
    "tenors = rates_dict.keys()\n",
    "rates = rates_dict.values()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.scatter(tenors, rates)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Calculo de curva sintética\n",
    "\n",
    "Las curvas sintéticas son calculadas automáticamente cuando se genera cualquier tipo de operación entre curvas, en este caso calcularemos la curva USD Local de manera sintética."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2023-10-11T20:36:30.660207100Z",
     "start_time": "2023-10-11T20:36:29.733301900Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>",
      "image/png": ""
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Necesitamos 3 curvas para\n",
    "clp_us_code = 'CLP FX'\n",
    "usd_us_code = 'USD SOFR'\n",
    "clp_cl_code = 'CLP_CAM'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Carga de datos\n",
    "reader.mx_origin = True\n",
    "CLP_US = reader.get_single_curve_data(curve_name=clp_us_code, process_date=curve_date, source=Source.SANDBOX)\n",
    "USD_US = reader.get_single_curve_data(curve_name=usd_us_code, process_date=curve_date, source=Source.SANDBOX)\n",
    "CLP_CL = reader.get_single_curve_data(curve_name=clp_cl_code, process_date=curve_date, source=Source.SANDBOX)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Creación de curva sintética\n",
    "USD_CL = (USD_US/CLP_US)*CLP_CL\n",
    "\n",
    "# Graficamos resultado\n",
    "tenors, rates = USD_CL.get_rate_curve()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.scatter(tenors, rates)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2023-10-11T20:36:31.046885300Z",
     "start_time": "2023-10-11T20:36:30.660207100Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>",
      "image/png": ""
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Comparación con Curva Oficial\n",
    "\n",
    "USD_CL = reader.get_single_curve_data(curve_name=\"CURVA_USD_CL\", process_date=curve_date, source=Source.OFFICIAL)\n",
    "# Graficamos resultado\n",
    "tenors, rates = USD_CL.get_rate_curve()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.scatter(tenors, rates)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Curva con Configuración personalizada\n",
    "\n",
    "Para generar una curva es necesario proveer un vector de tenors y factores de descuento con una fecha y nombre asociado, adicionalmente se puede proveer una configuración personalizada."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2023-10-11T20:36:31.046885300Z",
     "start_time": "2023-10-11T20:36:31.037845300Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Datos a utilizar\n",
    "tenors = [8, 15, 32, 63, 94, 126, 156, 185, 275, 367, 550, 735, 1099, 1463, 1828, 2194, 2559, 2926, 3290, 3655, 4385, 5481, 7308, 10962]\n",
    "dfs = [0.998310470000, 0.997016240000, 0.993143450000, 0.986344690000, 0.979086630000, 0.971138990000, 0.964269270000, 0.958115730000,\n",
    "0.938463220000, 0.923226950000, 0.898902260000, 0.873595740000, 0.834128950000, 0.793526060000, 0.749730130000, 0.711597520000,\n",
    "0.671697820000, 0.635942680000, 0.603079810000, 0.570977400000, 0.527430220000, 0.462406640000, 0.389123040000, 0.306809400000]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Configuración personalizada\n",
    "custom_config = generate_curve_config(interpolation_method=InterpolationMethod.LINEAR,\n",
    "                                      low_point_extrapolation_method=ExtrapolationMethod.SLOPE,\n",
    "                                      high_point_extrapolation_method=ExtrapolationMethod.FLAT,\n",
    "                                      rate_compounding=Compounding.YIELD,\n",
    "                                      rate_day_count=DayCount.DC_30_360)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Creación de curvas\n",
    "default_curve = Curve(curve_name=\"Default Config Curve\", process_date=curve_date, tenors=tenors, discount_factors=dfs)\n",
    "custom_curve = Curve(curve_name=\"Default Config Curve\", process_date=curve_date, tenors=tenors, discount_factors=dfs, curve_config=custom_config)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2023-10-11T20:36:31.060706100Z",
     "start_time": "2023-10-11T20:36:31.046885300Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "default:0.99314345 - custom:0.99314345\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Comparación 1\n",
    "\n",
    "d1 = default_curve.get_discount_factor(32)\n",
    "d2 = custom_curve.get_discount_factor(32)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"default:{d1} - custom:{d2}\".format(d1=d1, d2=d2))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2023-10-11T20:36:31.080259900Z",
     "start_time": "2023-10-11T20:36:31.060706100Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "default:0.07906308306385257 - custom:0.08519133793064726\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Comparación 2\n",
    "\n",
    "d1 = default_curve.get_rate(5)\n",
    "d2 = custom_curve.get_rate(5)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"default:{d1} - custom:{d2}\".format(d1=d1, d2=d2))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2023-10-11T20:36:31.152315700Z",
     "start_time": "2023-10-11T20:36:31.069740100Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "default:0.2891814894739244 - custom:0.3068094\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Comparación 3\n",
    "\n",
    "d1 = default_curve.get_discount_factor(35*365)\n",
    "d2 = custom_curve.get_discount_factor(35*365)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"default:{d1} - custom:{d2}\".format(d1=d1, d2=d2))"
   ]
  }
